    <h2><strong>Modern debate is broken:</strong></h2>
    <p>We're drowning in arguments and evidence — but everything’s <strong><a href="/w/page/21957405/duplication">repeated</a></strong>, <strong><a href="/w/page/21958998/order">disorganized</a></strong>, and <strong><a href="/disconnected" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">disconnected</a></strong>.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>We argue in circles — same points, no progress.</li>
      <li>No one links claims to shared evidence, so facts get lost in the noise.</li>
      <li>Beliefs get pushed without measuring real-world costs, benefits, or logic.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2><strong>What’s the fix?</strong></h2>
    <p>A platform that <strong>automates conflict resolution</strong>, <strong>ranks evidence</strong>, and <strong>structures cost‑benefit analysis</strong>. Let’s stop spinning our wheels and actually get somewhere.</p>
    <hr />

    <h3>Key Features</h3>
    <ol class="feature-list">
      <li><strong>Evidence-Driven Framework</strong></li>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="/w/page/159323433/One%20Page%20Per%20Topic">One page per topic:</a></strong> One structured page per debate — pros on one side, cons on the other.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/w/page/159300543/ReasonRank">ReasonRank:</a></strong> Like PageRank, but for arguments — ranked by logic, support, and impact.</li>
        <li><strong>Dynamic Scoring:</strong> Scores update as users add new evidence or counterpoints.</li>
      </ul>

      <li><strong>Analysis Tools for Smarter Decisions</strong></li>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="/w/page/156187122/cost-benefit%20analysis">Automated Cost‑Benefit Analysis:</a></strong> Brainstorm costs, benefits, and risks; use <a href="/w/page/159300543/ReasonRank">ReasonRank</a> to debate likelihoods.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/Likelihood%20Scores" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Likelihood Scores:</a></strong> Estimate how likely outcomes really are.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/w/page/159323226/Insisting%20on%20Objective%20Criteria">Maslow Mapping:</a></strong> Rate arguments by how well they meet human needs.</li>
      </ul>

      <li><strong>Built‑In Conflict Resolution</strong></li>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="/w/page/159323043/Focusing%20on%20Interests%2C%20Not%20Positions">Interest Mapping:</a></strong> Find shared goals and see where people actually agree.</li>
        <li><strong>Motivation Insight:</strong> See what’s driving each side — and how to address it.</li>
        <li><strong>Consensus Builders:</strong> Highlight overlap and nudge people toward agreement (or better arguments).</li>
      </ul>

      <li><strong>Smarter Content Management</strong></li>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Deduplication:</strong> Merge similar points into one cluster — one debate, not a thousand reruns.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="/Semantic%20Analysis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Semantic Precision:</a></strong> Cut the vague stuff and get to what’s actually being claimed.</li>
        <li><strong>Novelty Filters:</strong> Surface fresh arguments — no more déjà vu.</li>
      </ul>
    </ol>

    <h3>How It Works</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>User Participation:</strong> Add arguments, attach evidence, rate counterpoints.</li>
      <li><strong>Community Moderation:</strong> No censorship. Weak arguments drop; strong ones float — with reasons.</li>
    </ul>

